704517f-a.text:
Fulton Street, east from Joralemon Street. At the right, on Joralemon Street, are the King's County Court House and the Hall of Record, followed by the King's County Trust Co. At the left, the Citizen Building houses the "Brooklyn Daily Citizen". The Boerum Place station of the Fulto
Street elevated lines may also be seen.
About 1900.

705167f.text:
Joralemon Street, south side, at Fulton Street. A view of Kings
County Court.
1910.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

704516f-a.text:
Fulton Street, at its intersection with Joralemon, Adams and Willeughby Streets, showing the Fulton Street Elevated line of the B.M.T. TRe center building is the City Hall, with the Brooklyn Citizen's Bank Building on the
left.
About 1910.
Eugene L. Armbruster Cellection.
704516f-a.folder: Fulton Street & Joralemon Street, Brooklyn, NY

704518f-a.text:
Fulton Street (elevated structure thereon), south side, east from its intersection with Joralemon Street, showing a general view southeastward as seen from the Temple Bar Building which is located on the west side of Court Street (No. 44) at the N.W. corner of Joralemon Street. At the right of the Fulton Street Elevated line, beginning with the foreground, are in their order, the following buildings; namely, the new and old Munteipal Buildings, and the Hall of Records. The triangular roofed building to the left is at the intersection of Wtlloughby and Fulton Streets. The
elevated station is on Boerum Place.
May 1926.
Brown Brothers.
704518f-a.folder: Fulton Street & Joralemon Street, Brooklyn, NY

702948f-a.text:
Adams Street, west side, south to Fulton Street, from 366 at right foreground. In the background, is seen the Fulton Street "Elevated" structure, and the Hall of Aecords building; to the right of them, is a building oocupied by the "Brooklyn Daily Citizen", established in 1386. It was built by one Jones in 1842, and was the first home of the N. Y. & N. J. Telephone
Co., of Brooklyn.
1928.
Eugene L Armbruster Collection.
702948f-a.folder: Adams Street & Fulton Street, Brooklyn, NY

705168f-a.text: Joralemon Street, south side, from but not including Boerum Place, to but not including Court Street. The view shown is the Brooklyn Municipal Building. In the background, is the upper part of the Chamber of Commerce Building at 60 Court Street. About 1930.
